FT  08 SEP 94 / Observer: Fingered
Russians seem to have a sweet tooth - and are willing to pay for it. In
return for the 200 tonnes of Cadbury's chocolate fingers Hillsdown Holdings
sold to Russia this year it has received hard cash. No bartering, and
absolutely no attempt to pay for the nibbles in plutonium. But, says chief
executive David Newton, finance director Raymond Mackie has been known to
light up in the dark. . .
